author: Jenny Hsu
title: Oil Prices Reap Slight Gains on Weaker Dollar
text: 0145 GMT [Dow Jones] Oil prices are slightly higher on the back of a weaker dollar spurred by the soft U.S. September non-farm payroll data, says an ANZ Research report. A weaker job market decreases the chance for the Federal Reserve to raise interest rates later this year, the report adds. “But sell-off pressure is still strong. Saudi Arabia’s decision to cut prices amid the price slump shows Asia demands are actually lower than expected,” says Barnabas Gan, an OCBC oil analyst, tipping oil prices could stay lower for longer with Nymex and Brent finding support at $40/bbl and $45/bbl, respectively.
